## Customer focused

### Feedback

We use [Hotjar](https://insights.hotjar.com/sites/709549/dashboard) for getting feedback through questionnaires as well as heatmaps\. [Google Analytics](https://analytics.google.com/analytics/web/) is used for tracking\. 

### Web shop

Web sales is fulfilled using [SendOwl](https://sendowl.com)  [ChargeBee](https://jumpto365.chargebee.com/dashboards) \([test here](https://codepen.io/niegrejoh/live/qJvpxw)\) and cashed\-in using [Stripe](https://www.stripe.com) \. 

### Licenses

Licenses is managed using Azure Logic Apps, where the [Licensing Logic App](https://portal.azure.com/#@365admin.net/resource/subscriptions/8018d1a9-2d4c-4af6-9dcf-1e27709314ca/resourceGroups/365admin/providers/Microsoft.Logic/workflows/Licensing/logicApp) does the job\. The logic app is wrapped by an [Azure Function](https://jumpto365demo.scm.azurewebsites.net/dev/wwwroot/flow/index.js) \- [Source code](https://365admin.visualstudio.com/Jumpto365/_git/pto365-functions)

Intra365 for Word 

area: Microsoft Partner Qualifications 

To get qualifying point towards an ISV silver competence a registration in [Office Store](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/office/dev/store/submit-to-the-office-store) is needed

## Operations

### Azure Portal

Everything is hosted in Azure, on a regular basis I check the [Error logs](https://portal.azure.com/#blade/HubsExtension/Resources/resourceType/microsoft.insights%2Fcomponents) and [Subscription Costs](https://portal.azure.com/#blade/Microsoft_Azure_Billing/ModernBillingMenuBlade/Overview)\. I also now and then checks the general application health using [Application Insights](https://portal.azure.com/#@365admin.net/resource/subscriptions/f2be2d48-417f-4f4f-900a-542941227086/resourceGroups/Jumpto365/providers/microsoft.insights/components/periodictableoffice365/overview)

### Azure DevOps

Formerly know as Visual Studio Team Services, I use the [Jumpto365](https://365admin.visualstudio.com/Jumpto365/_dashboards/Jumpto365%20Team/61629cf0-a901-463d-9974-ddad77461ef8) project for keeping track of backlogs, storing code and publishing versions\. When I publish a new version I manually have to purge the [CDN](https://portal.azure.com/#@365admin.net/resource/subscriptions/f2be2d48-417f-4f4f-900a-542941227086/resourcegroups/Jumpto365/providers/Microsoft.Cdn/profiles/icansharepoint/endpoints/pto365-test/overview) ![](data:image/png;base64,)
